**Damage Report:**

**Vehicle Make/Model:** [Insert Vehicle Information]
**Date of Inspection:** [Insert Date]

**Location of Damage:**
- The front fender of the vehicle shows visible damage near the wheel well area.

**Type of Damage:**
- The damage appears to be a dent or indentation on the fender, likely caused by an impact. There is also a small scratch or scuff mark visible on the surface of the fender.

**Additional Notes:**
- The dent is located towards the lower portion of the fender, close to where it meets the wheel well.
- The scratch/scuff mark is located above the dent and seems to be a minor abrasion.

**Conclusion:**
The vehicle has sustained damage to the front fender, which requires repair. The extent of the damage will need to be assessed further with the assistance of a professional mechanic or body shop.
